CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 12, 1954, pg. 1, reads: "Store Strike Safari - This is the all-Negro group of messengers who carry packages, safari-like, from department stores to the post office through the Downtown streets numerous times during the day since the advent of the strike by department store unions. The travel always in a full group, and are given heavy protection, since they draw the ire of pickets. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Men, department store messengers, carrying boxes and bundles along Grant Street, across from Koppers Building and in front of Embassy Restaurant, Downtown
